66 struct bgpstream_elem_generator {
67 
69  bgpstream_elem_t **elems;
70 
72  int elems_cnt;
73 
75  int elems_alloc_cnt;
76 
77  /* Current iterator position (iter == cnt means end-of-list) */
78  int iter;
79 };

83 static bgpstream_elem_t *get_new_elem(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self)
84 {
85  bgpstream_elem_t *elem = NULL;
86 
87  /* check if we need to alloc more elems */
88  if(self->elems_cnt+1 >= self->elems_alloc_cnt)
89  {
90 
91  /* alloc more memory */
92  if((self->elems =
93  realloc(self->elems, sizeof(bgpstream_elem_t*) *
94  (self->elems_alloc_cnt+1))) == NULL)
95  {
96  return NULL;
97  }
98 
99  /* create an elem */
100  if((self->elems[self->elems_alloc_cnt] = bgpstream_elem_create()) == NULL)
101  {
102  return NULL;
103  }
104 
105  self->elems_alloc_cnt++;
106  }
107 
108  elem = self->elems[self->elems_cnt++];
109  bgpstream_elem_clear(elem);
110  return elem;
111 }

117 static void get_aspath_struct(struct aspath *ap,
118  bgpstream_as_path_t *bs_ap)
119 {
120  const char *invalid_characters = "([{}])";
121  // char origin_copy[16];
122  uint32_t it;
123  char * tok = NULL;
124  char *c = ap->str;
125  char *next;
126  bs_ap->hop_count = ap->count;
127  bs_ap->type = BGPSTREAM_AS_TYPE_UNKNOWN;
128 
129  if(ap->str == NULL || bs_ap->hop_count == 0) {
130  // aspath is empty, if it is an internal AS bgp info that is fine
131  return;
132  }
133  // check if there are sets or confederations
134  while (*c) {
135  if(strchr(invalid_characters, *c)) {
136  bs_ap->type = BGPSTREAM_AS_TYPE_STRING;
137  bs_ap->str_aspath = NULL;
138  break;
139  }
140  c++;
141  }
142  /* if sets or confederations are present, then
143  * the AS_PATH is of type STRING */
144  if(bs_ap->type == BGPSTREAM_AS_TYPE_STRING) {
145  /* if the type is STR then we allocate the memory
146  * required for the path - we do not copy ap->str
147  * it is a fixed length array which is unreasonably
148  long (8000)*/
149  bs_ap->str_aspath = strdup(ap->str);
150 
152  assert(bs_ap->str_aspath);
153  }
154 
155  /* if type has not been changed, then it is numeric, then */
156 
157  if(bs_ap->type == BGPSTREAM_AS_TYPE_UNKNOWN)
158  {
159  bs_ap->type = BGPSTREAM_AS_TYPE_NUMERIC;
160  it = 0;
161  bs_ap->numeric_aspath = (uint32_t *)malloc(bs_ap->hop_count * sizeof(uint32_t));
163  if(bs_ap->numeric_aspath == NULL) {
164  bgpstream_log_err("get_aspath_struct: can't malloc aspath numeric array");
165  assert(0);
166  return;
167  }
168 
169  next = c = strdup(ap->str);
170  while((tok = strsep(&next, " ")) != NULL) {
171  if(it == bs_ap->hop_count)
172  {
173  fprintf(stderr, "Wrong hop count %d - %s\n", bs_ap->hop_count, ap->str);
174  assert(0);
175  }
176  // strcpy(origin_copy, tok);
177  bs_ap->numeric_aspath[it] = strtoul(tok, NULL, 10);
178  it++;
179  }
180  free(c);
181  }
182 
183 }

186 /* ribs related functions */
187 static int table_line_mrtd_route(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self,
188  BGPDUMP_ENTRY *entry) {
189 
190  bgpstream_elem_t *ri;
191  if((ri = get_new_elem(self)) == NULL)
192  {
193  return -1;
194  }
195 
196  // general
197  ri->type = BGPSTREAM_ELEM_TYPE_RIB;
198  ri->timestamp = entry->time;
199 
200  // peer and prefix
201  if (entry->subtype == AFI_IP6)
202  {
203  ri->peer_address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV6;
204  ri->peer_address.ipv6 = entry->body.mrtd_table_dump.peer_ip.v6_addr;
205  ri->prefix.address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV6;
206  ri->prefix.address.ipv6 = entry->body.mrtd_table_dump.prefix.v6_addr;
207  }
208  else
209  {
210  ri->peer_address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
211  ri->peer_address.ipv4 = entry->body.mrtd_table_dump.peer_ip.v4_addr;
212  ri->prefix.address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
213  ri->prefix.address.ipv4 = entry->body.mrtd_table_dump.prefix.v4_addr;
214  }
215  ri->prefix.mask_len = entry->body.mrtd_table_dump.mask;
216  ri->peer_asnumber = entry->body.mrtd_table_dump.peer_as;
217 
218  // as path
219  if(entry->attr->flag & ATTR_FLAG_BIT(BGP_ATTR_AS_PATH) &&
220  entry->attr->aspath)
221  {
222  bgpstream_as_path_populate(ri->aspath, entry->attr->aspath);
223  }
224 
225  // nextop
226  if((entry->attr->flag & ATTR_FLAG_BIT(BGP_ATTR_MP_REACH_NLRI)) &&
227  entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST])
228  {
229  ri->nexthop.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV6;
230  ri->nexthop.ipv6 =
231  entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST]->nexthop.v6_addr;
232  }
233  else
234  {
235  ri->nexthop.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
236  ri->nexthop.ipv4 = entry->attr->nexthop;
237  }
238  return 0;
239 }

241 int table_line_dump_v2_prefix(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self,
242  BGPDUMP_ENTRY *entry) {
243  bgpstream_elem_t *ri;
244 
245  BGPDUMP_TABLE_DUMP_V2_PREFIX *e = &(entry->body.mrtd_table_dump_v2_prefix);
246  int i;
247 
248  for(i = 0; i < e->entry_count; i++) {
249  attributes_t *attr = e->entries[i].attr;
250  if(! attr)
251  continue;
252 
253  if((ri = get_new_elem(self)) == NULL)
254  {
255  return -1;
256  }
257 
258  // general info
259  ri->type = BGPSTREAM_ELEM_TYPE_RIB;
260  ri->timestamp = entry->time;
261 
262  // peer
263  if(e->entries[i].peer.afi == AFI_IP){
264  ri->peer_address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
265  ri->peer_address.ipv4 = e->entries[i].peer.peer_ip.v4_addr;
266  }
267  else {
268  if(e->entries[i].peer.afi == AFI_IP6){
269  ri->peer_address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV6;
270  ri->peer_address.ipv6 = e->entries[i].peer.peer_ip.v6_addr;
271  }
272  else {
273  return -1;
274  }
275  }
276 
277  ri->peer_asnumber = e->entries[i].peer.peer_as;
278 
279  // prefix
280  if(e->afi == AFI_IP) {
281  ri->prefix.address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
282  ri->prefix.address.ipv4 = e->prefix.v4_addr;
283  }
284  else{
285  if(e->afi == AFI_IP6) {
286  ri->prefix.address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV6;
287  ri->prefix.address.ipv6 = e->prefix.v6_addr;
288  }
289  }
290  ri->prefix.mask_len = e->prefix_length;
291  // as path
292  if (attr->aspath) {
293  bgpstream_as_path_populate(ri->aspath, attr->aspath);
294  }
295  // next hop
296  if ((attr->flag & ATTR_FLAG_BIT(BGP_ATTR_MP_REACH_NLRI)) &&
297  attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST]) {
298  ri->nexthop.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV6;
299  ri->nexthop.ipv6 = attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST]->nexthop.v6_addr;
300  }
301  else
302  {
303  ri->nexthop.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
304  ri->nexthop.ipv4 = attr->nexthop;
305  }
306 
307  }
308  return 0;
309 }

311 static int table_line_announce(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self,
312  struct prefix *prefix, int count,
313  BGPDUMP_ENTRY *entry){
314  bgpstream_elem_t * ri;
315  int idx;
316  for (idx=0;idx<count;idx++) {
317  if((ri = get_new_elem(self)) == NULL)
318  {
319  return -1;
320  }
321 
322  // general info
323  ri->type = BGPSTREAM_ELEM_TYPE_ANNOUNCEMENT;
324  ri->timestamp = entry->time;
325  // peer
326  if(entry->body.zebra_message.address_family == AFI_IP6) {
327  ri->peer_address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV6;
328  ri->peer_address.ipv6 = entry->body.zebra_message.source_ip.v6_addr;
329  }
330  if(entry->body.zebra_message.address_family == AFI_IP) {
331  ri->peer_address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
332  ri->peer_address.ipv4 = entry->body.zebra_message.source_ip.v4_addr;
333  }
334  ri->peer_asnumber = entry->body.zebra_message.source_as;
335  // prefix (ipv4)
336  ri->prefix.address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
337  ri->prefix.address.ipv4 = prefix[idx].address.v4_addr;
338  ri->prefix.mask_len = prefix[idx].len;
339  // nexthop (ipv4)
340  ri->nexthop.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
341  ri->nexthop.ipv4 = entry->attr->nexthop;
342  // as path
343  if(entry->attr->flag & ATTR_FLAG_BIT(BGP_ATTR_AS_PATH) &&
344  entry->attr->aspath) {
345  bgpstream_as_path_populate(ri->aspath, entry->attr->aspath);
346  }
347  }
348  return 0;
349 }

499 static int table_line_update(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self,
500  BGPDUMP_ENTRY *entry) {
501  struct prefix *prefix;
502  struct mp_nlri *prefix_mp;
503  int count;
504 
505  // withdrawals (IPv4)
506  if ((entry->body.zebra_message.withdraw_count) ||
507  (entry->attr->flag & ATTR_FLAG_BIT(BGP_ATTR_MP_UNREACH_NLRI))) {
508  prefix = entry->body.zebra_message.withdraw;
509  count = entry->body.zebra_message.withdraw_count;
510  if(table_line_withdraw(self, prefix, count, entry) != 0)
511  {
512  return -1;
513  }
514  }
515  if (entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST] &&
516  entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST]->prefix_count){
517  prefix = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST]->nlri;
518  count = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST]->prefix_count;
519  if(table_line_withdraw(self, prefix, count, entry) != 0)
520  {
521  return -1;
522  }
523  }
524  if (entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_MULTICAST] &&
525  entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_MULTICAST]->prefix_count) {
526  prefix = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_MULTICAST]->nlri;
527  count = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_MULTICAST]->prefix_count;
528  if(table_line_withdraw(self, prefix, count, entry) != 0)
529  {
530  return -1;
531  }
532  }
533  if (entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST] &&
534  entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->prefix_count) {
535  prefix = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->nlri;
536  count = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->prefix_count;
537  if(table_line_withdraw(self, prefix, count, entry) != 0)
538  {
539  return -1;
540  }
541  }
542 
543  // withdrawals (IPv6)
544  if (entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST] &&
545  entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST]->prefix_count) {
546  prefix = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST]->nlri;
547  count = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST]->prefix_count;
548  if(table_line_withdraw6(self, prefix, count, entry) != 0)
549  {
550  return -1;
551  }
552  }
553  if (entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_MULTICAST] &&
554  entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_MULTICAST]->prefix_count) {
555  prefix = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_MULTICAST]->nlri;
556  count = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_MULTICAST]->prefix_count;
557  if(table_line_withdraw6(self, prefix, count, entry) != 0)
558  {
559  return -1;
560  }
561  }
562  if (entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST] &&
563  entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->prefix_count) {
564  prefix = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->nlri;
565  count = entry->attr->mp_info->withdraw[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->prefix_count;
566  if(table_line_withdraw6(self, prefix, count, entry) != 0)
567  {
568  return -1;
569  }
570  }
571 
572  // announce
573  if ( (entry->body.zebra_message.announce_count) ||
574  (entry->attr->flag & ATTR_FLAG_BIT(BGP_ATTR_MP_REACH_NLRI))) {
575  prefix = entry->body.zebra_message.announce;
576  count = entry->body.zebra_message.announce_count;
577  if(table_line_announce(self, prefix, count, entry) != 0)
578  {
579  return -1;
580  }
581  }
582 
583  // announce 1
584  if (entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST] &&
585  entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST]->prefix_count) {
586  prefix_mp = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST];
587  count = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST]->prefix_count;
588  if(table_line_announce_1(self, prefix_mp, count, entry) != 0)
589  {
590  return -1;
591  }
592  }
593  if (entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_MULTICAST] &&
594  entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_MULTICAST]->prefix_count) {
595  prefix_mp = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_MULTICAST];
596  count = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_MULTICAST]->prefix_count;
597  if(table_line_announce_1(self, prefix_mp, count, entry) != 0)
598  {
599  return -1;
600  }
601  }
602  if (entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST] &&
603  entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->prefix_count) {
604  prefix_mp = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST];
605  count = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->prefix_count;
606  if(table_line_announce_1(self, prefix_mp, count, entry) != 0)
607  {
608  return -1;
609  }
610  }
611 
612  // announce ipv6
613  if (entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST] &&
614  entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST]->prefix_count) {
615  prefix_mp = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST];
616  count = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST]->prefix_count;
617  if(table_line_announce6(self, prefix_mp, count, entry) != 0)
618  {
619  return -1;
620  }
621  }
622  if (entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_MULTICAST] &&
623  entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_MULTICAST]->prefix_count) {
624  prefix_mp = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_MULTICAST];
625  count = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_MULTICAST]->prefix_count;
626  if(table_line_announce6(self, prefix_mp, count, entry) != 0)
627  {
628  return -1;
629  }
630  }
631  if (entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST] &&
632  entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->prefix_count) {
633  prefix_mp = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST];
634  count = entry->attr->mp_info->announce[AFI_IP6][SAFI_UNICAST_MULTICAST]->prefix_count;
635  if(table_line_announce6(self, prefix_mp, count, entry) != 0)
636  {
637  return -1;
638  }
639  }
640 
641  return 0;
642 }
643 
644 static int bgp_state_change(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self,
645  BGPDUMP_ENTRY *entry) {
646  bgpstream_elem_t * ri;
647  if((ri = get_new_elem(self)) == NULL)
648  {
649  return -1;
650  }
651 
652  // general information
653  ri->type = BGPSTREAM_ELEM_TYPE_PEERSTATE;
654  ri->timestamp = entry->time;
655  // peer
656  if(entry->body.zebra_message.address_family == AFI_IP6) {
657  ri->peer_address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV6;
658  ri->peer_address.ipv6 = entry->body.zebra_state_change.source_ip.v6_addr;
659  }
660  if(entry->body.zebra_message.address_family == AFI_IP) {
661  ri->peer_address.version = BGPSTREAM_ADDR_VERSION_IPV4;
662  ri->peer_address.ipv4 = entry->body.zebra_state_change.source_ip.v4_addr;
663  }
664  ri->peer_asnumber = entry->body.zebra_message.source_as;
665  ri->old_state = entry->body.zebra_state_change.old_state;
666  ri->new_state = entry->body.zebra_state_change.new_state;
667  return 0;
668 }

672 bgpstream_elem_generator_t *bgpstream_elem_generator_create()
673 {
674  bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self;
675 
676  if((self = malloc_zero(sizeof(bgpstream_elem_generator_t))) == NULL)
677  {
678  return NULL;
679  }
680 
681  /* indicates not populated */
682  self->elems_cnt = -1;
683 
684  return self;
685 }
686 
687 void bgpstream_elem_generator_destroy(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self)
688 {
689  int i;
690  if(self == NULL)
691  {
692  return;
693  }
694 
695  /* free all the alloc'd elems */
696  for(i=0; i<self->elems_alloc_cnt; i++)
697  {
698  bgpstream_elem_destroy(self->elems[i]);
699  self->elems[i] = NULL;
700  }
701 
702  free(self->elems);
703 
704  self->elems_cnt = self->elems_alloc_cnt = self->iter = 0;
705 
706  free(self);
707 }
708 
709 void bgpstream_elem_generator_clear(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self)
710 {
711  /* explicit clear is done by get_next_elem */
712 
713  self->elems_cnt = -1;
714  self->iter = 0;
715 }
716 
717 int bgpstream_elem_generator_is_populated(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self)
718 {
719  return self->elems_cnt != -1;
720 }
721 
722 int bgpstream_elem_generator_populate(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self,
723  bgpstream_record_t *record)
724 {
725  assert(record != NULL);
726 
727  /* bgpstream_record must have cleared already */
728  assert(self->elems_cnt == -1);
729 
730  /* start with an empty set */
731  self->elems_cnt = 0;
732 
733  if(record->bd_entry == NULL ||
734  record->status != BGPSTREAM_RECORD_STATUS_VALID_RECORD)
735  {
736  return 0;
737  }
738 
739  switch(record->bd_entry->type)
740  {
741  case BGPDUMP_TYPE_MRTD_TABLE_DUMP:
742  return table_line_mrtd_route(self, record->bd_entry);
743  break;
744 
745  case BGPDUMP_TYPE_TABLE_DUMP_V2:
746  return table_line_dump_v2_prefix(self, record->bd_entry);
747  break;
748 
749  case BGPDUMP_TYPE_ZEBRA_BGP:
750  switch(record->bd_entry->subtype)
751  {
752  case BGPDUMP_SUBTYPE_ZEBRA_BGP_MESSAGE:
753  case BGPDUMP_SUBTYPE_ZEBRA_BGP_MESSAGE_AS4:
754  switch(record->bd_entry->body.zebra_message.type)
755  {
756  case BGP_MSG_UPDATE:
757  return table_line_update(self, record->bd_entry);
758  break;
759  }
760  break;
761 
762  case BGPDUMP_SUBTYPE_ZEBRA_BGP_STATE_CHANGE: // state messages
763  case BGPDUMP_SUBTYPE_ZEBRA_BGP_STATE_CHANGE_AS4:
764  return bgp_state_change(self, record->bd_entry);
765  break;
766  }
767  }
768  return -1;
769 }

771 bgpstream_elem_t *
772 bgpstream_elem_generator_get_next_elem(bgpstream_elem_generator_t *self)
773 {
774  bgpstream_elem_t *elem = NULL;
775 
776  if(self->iter < self->elems_cnt)
777  {
778  elem = self->elems[self->iter];
779  self->iter++;
780  }
781 
782  return elem;
783 }
